author: John Woodrow Cox
title: Jim Webb’s withdrawal is the Democrats’ loss
text:
Former Virginia senator Jim Webb this week. (Andrew Harnik/Associated Press) October 23 at 4:55 PM Former senator Jim Webb’s (D-Va.) withdrawal from the Democratic presidential primary campaign is a loss for the Democratic Party [“ Webb exits Democratic presidential race, will weigh run as independent ,” news, Oct. 21]. Although the erratic nature of Mr. Webb’s career moves must share the blame for his lack of political traction, the short shrift that he was given by self-anointed “progressive” pundits reflects the shallowness of their political awareness.
